{{authority control}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Afrah, Mohamed}} [[:Category:Living people]] [[:Category:People from Malé]] [[:Category:21st-century Maldivian actresses]] [[:Category:Maldivian film actors]]

{{Infobox person | name = Mohamed Afrah | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | nationality = Maldivian | alma_mater = | occupation = Actor, journalist | yearsactive = 2019–present | spouse = | partner = | children = | works = | awards = }}
'''Mohamed Waheed''' is a Maldivian journalist and film actor.
==Career== In 2019, he made his film career debut in Maldivian first sitcom ''[[Karu Hakuru]]'' developed by Mohamed Munthasir.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sun.mv/116740 |title=Maldivian first sit-com "Karu Hakuru" available for streaming |work=Sun |language=Divehi |last=Lubaa |first=Aminath |date=14 March 2019 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190814082157/https://sun.mv/116740 |archivedate=14 August 2019 |accessdate=13 August 2019 |df=dmy-all |url-status=live }}</ref> His performance as the nosy neighbor and the series received positive reviews from critics.<ref name=KaruHakuruReview>{{cite news |url=https://dho.mv/baiscope/51680 |title=Lamha brings the require nuance to Karu Hakuru |work=Dho? |language=Divehi |last=Maaha |first=Aishath |date=14 March 2019 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190813104116/https://dho.mv/baiscope/51680 |archivedate=13 August 2019 |accessdate=13 August 2019 |df=dmy-all |url-status=live }}</ref> He next appeared in Ilyas Waheed's psychological thriller film ''[[Bavathi]]'' (2019), where he played the role of Zahir, XX. The film narrates the story of a woman who relocates to Male' after marriage and the strange incidents that follow afterwards.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/13378 |title=Teaser of Bavathi released |language=Divehi |work=MuniAvas |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=1 April 2019 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190508152220/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/52666 |archivedate=8 May 2019 |accessdate=8 May 2019 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film received positive reviews from critics, where Ifraz Ali from ''Dho?'' credited the film with a four star rating and applauded the screenplay for its "tight suspense" while Aminath Luba reviewing from ''Sun'' opined that ''Bavathi'' will go down the history lane as an "unexpected masterpiece".<ref name=DhoReview>{{cite news |url=https://dho.mv/baiscope/60708 |title=Bavathi: An expermiental wonder |language=Divehi |work=Dho? |last=Ali |first=Ifraz |date=5 September 2019 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190910084709/https://dho.mv/baiscope/60708 |archivedate=10 September 2019 |accessdate=10 September 2019 |df=dmy-all |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=SunReview>{{cite news |url=https://sun.mv/123842 |title=Bavathi: Exceeds viewers' expectation |language=Divehi |work=Sun |last=Luba |first=Aminath |date=6 September 2019 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190910090226/https://sun.mv/123842 |archivedate=10 September 2019 |accessdate=10 September 2019 |df=dmy-all |url-status=live }}</ref>
In 2022, he had multiple releases. He first appeared in a supporting role as a father who abandoned his daughter in [[Ahmed Nimal]] directed web series ''[[Lafuzu]]''.<ref name=Lafuzu>{{cite news|url=https://www.sun.mv/162522 |title=Muhamma's "Lafuzu" launched as a MediaNet Original |work=Sun |language=Divehi |date=27 February 2022 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220412112027/https://www.sun.mv/162522 |url-status=live |archivedate=12 April 2022 |accessdate=12 April 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/40244 |title=Muhamma's "Lafuzu" premiered |work=MuniAvas |language=Divehi |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=26 February 2022 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220227125835/https://www.muniavas.com/40244 |url-status=live |archivedate=27 February 2022 |accessdate=27 February 2022}}</ref>
He then played the role of Shiflyn, an over enthusiastic and bubbly character in the office comedy sitcom ''[[Office Loabi]]'' developed by Amyna Mohamed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/40531 |title="Office Loabi to Baiskoafu |language=Divehi |work=MuniAvas |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=2 April 2022 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220402165618/https://www.muniavas.com/40531 |url-status= live |archivedate=2 April 2022 |accessdate=2 April 2022|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The series along with her performance received positive reviews from critics, where Ahmed Rasheed from ''MuniAvas'' praised the performance of Mariyam Waheedha, in particular while highlighting the "excellent integration of a unique concept to the viewers".<ref name=release>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/40531 |title="Office Loabi to Baiskoafu |language=Divehi |work=MuniAvas |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=2 April 2022 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220402165618/https://www.muniavas.com/40531 |url-status= live |archivedate=2 April 2022 |accessdate=2 April 2022|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Reviewing the first episode of the series,
