{{Infobox person | name = Mohamed Afrah | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | nationality = Maldivian | alma_mater = | occupation = Actor, journalist | yearsactive = 2019–present | spouse = | partner = | children = | works = | awards = }}
'''Mohamed Waheed''' is a Maldivian journalist and film actor.
==Career== In 2019, he made his film career debut in Maldivian first sitcom ''[[Karu Hakuru]]'' developed by Mohamed Munthasir.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sun.mv/116740 |title=Maldivian first sit-com "Karu Hakuru" available for streaming |work=Sun |language=Divehi |last=Lubaa |first=Aminath |date=14 March 2019 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190814082157/https://sun.mv/116740 |archivedate=14 August 2019 |accessdate=13 August 2019 |df=dmy-all |url-status=live }}</ref> His performance as the nosy neighbor and the series received positive reviews from critics.<ref name=KaruHakuruReview>{{cite news |url=https://dho.mv/baiscope/51680 |title=Lamha brings the require nuance to Karu Hakuru |work=Dho? |language=Divehi |last=Maaha |first=Aishath |date=14 March 2019 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190813104116/https://dho.mv/baiscope/51680 |archivedate=13 August 2019 |accessdate=13 August 2019 |df=dmy-all |url-status=live }}</ref> He next appeared in Ilyas Waheed's psychological thriller film ''[[Bavathi]]'' (2019), where he played the role of Zahir, a middle aged man who performs ruqyah on a disturbed couple. The film narrates the story of a woman who relocates to Male' after marriage and the strange incidents that follow afterwards.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/13378 |title=Teaser of Bavathi released |language=Divehi |work=MuniAvas |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=1 April 2019 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190508152220/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/52666 |archivedate=8 May 2019 |accessdate=8 May 2019 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film received positive reviews from critics, where Ifraz Ali from ''Dho?'' credited the film with a four star rating and applauded the screenplay for its "tight suspense" while Aminath Luba reviewing from ''Sun'' opined that ''Bavathi'' will go down the history lane as an "unexpected masterpiece".<ref name=DhoReview>{{cite news |url=https://dho.mv/baiscope/60708 |title=Bavathi: An expermiental wonder |language=Divehi |work=Dho? |last=Ali |first=Ifraz |date=5 September 2019 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190910084709/https://dho.mv/baiscope/60708 |archivedate=10 September 2019 |accessdate=10 September 2019 |df=dmy-all |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=SunReview>{{cite news |url=https://sun.mv/123842 |title=Bavathi: Exceeds viewers' expectation |language=Divehi |work=Sun |last=Luba |first=Aminath |date=6 September 2019 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190910090226/https://sun.mv/123842 |archivedate=10 September 2019 |accessdate=10 September 2019 |df=dmy-all |url-status=live }}</ref>
He then collaborated with [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]] for ''[[Giridha]]'' (2021), featuring alongside [[Ibrahim Jihad]], [[Ali Azim]], Ali Usam and [[Ahmed Ziya]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://hurihaa.mv/7678 |title="Giridha"'s to be streamed on September 7 |work=Hurihaa |language=Divehi |date=30 August 2021 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118080532/https://hurihaa.mv/7678 |url-status=live |archivedate=18 January 2022 |accessdate=18 January 2022}}</ref> Developed as a hybrid of "sitcom and casual comedy", the series follows three friends who move to Male' in hopes of finding work and lures their lessor to fund for their dream film project.<ref name=Giridha>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/37237 |title=Eupe's "Giridha" for Medianet OTT |work=MuniAvas |language=Divehi |last=Dheema |first=Mariyam |date=7 August 2021 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210910101142/https://www.muniavas.com/37237 |url-status=live |archivedate=10 September 2021 |accessdate=10 September 2021}}</ref>
In 2022, he had multiple releases. He first appeared in a supporting role as a father who abandoned his daughter in [[Ahmed Nimal]] directed web series ''[[Lafuzu]]''.<ref name=Lafuzu>{{cite news|url=https://www.sun.mv/162522 |title=Muhamma's "Lafuzu" launched as a MediaNet Original |work=Sun |language=Divehi |date=27 February 2022 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220412112027/https://www.sun.mv/162522 |url-status=live |archivedate=12 April 2022 |accessdate=12 April 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/40244 |title=Muhamma's "Lafuzu" premiered |work=MuniAvas |language=Divehi |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=26 February 2022 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220227125835/https://www.muniavas.com/40244 |url-status=live |archivedate=27 February 2022 |accessdate=27 February 2022}}</ref>
He then played the role of Shiflyn, an over enthusiastic and bubbly character in the office comedy sitcom ''[[Office Loabi]]'' developed by Amyna Mohamed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/40531 |title="Office Loabi to Baiskoafu |language=Divehi |work=MuniAvas |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=2 April 2022 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220402165618/https://www.muniavas.com/40531 |url-status= live |archivedate=2 April 2022 |accessdate=2 April 2022|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The series along with her performance received positive reviews from critics, where Ahmed Rasheed from ''MuniAvas'' praised the performance of Afrah in particular, in particular while highlighting the "excellent integration of a unique concept to the viewers".<ref name=release>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/40531 |title="Office Loabi to Baiskoafu |language=Divehi |work=MuniAvas |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=2 April 2022 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220402165618/https://www.muniavas.com/40531 |url-status= live |archivedate=2 April 2022 |accessdate=2 April 2022|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
He also starred in Azhan Ibrahim's crime thriller web series ''[[Dharaka]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/38678 |title=Web series "Dharaka" coming soon |language=Divehi |work=MuniAvas |last=Abdullah |first=Saajid |date=1 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211091612/https://www.muniavas.com/38678 |url-status= live |archive-date=11 December 2021 |access-date=11 December 2021 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The series revolves around a high-profile case of the disappearance of a politician's daughter.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/40399 |title="Dharaka" to be released on 8 April |work=MuniAvas |language=Divehi |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=15 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220315162751/https://www.muniavas.com/40399 |url-status=live |archive-date=15 March 2022 |access-date=15 March 2022 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Reviewing the finale of the series, Ahmed Rasheed from ''MuniAvas'' considered the series to be an "excellent watch, if you are interested in good quality series".<ref name=Dharaka>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/41172 |title=Nisha's murderer revealed |work=MuniAvas |language=Divehi |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=20 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220812055220/https://www.muniavas.com/41172 |url-status=live |archive-date=12 August 2022 |access-date=12 August 2022 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
He also starred in Bahaulla Ibrahim's family drama television series ''[[Shakuvaa]]'' alongside [[Ahmed Easa]], [[Nathasha Jaleel]] and [[Nuzuhath Shuaib]], playing the supportive friend of the lead actor.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.muniavas.com/40540 |title="Lift Golhi" of "Vihaal" released |work=MuniAvas |language=Divehi |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=3 April 2022 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220405091157/https://www.muniavas.com/40540 |url-status=live |archivedate=5 April 2022 |accessdate=5 April 2022 }}</ref>
